- DDL loader ignores index DDL and only processes CreateTable (codegen/loader.go:233-295).
- Prior research adopted Option C / Query-first / manual-guidance baseline and treated metadata parity as the prerequisite before any future index-helper direction.

## Constraints
- Do not broaden the generated public API beyond the current CRUD + FindByPrimaryKey surface.
- Keep SpannerDB as ReadRow + Query.
- Do not implement generic query builders, pagination abstractions, or repository/runtime layers.
- Prefer minimal, reviewable code changes with tests.

## Unknowns / open questions
- Exact live metadata fields needed for future evaluation (index columns only vs STORING coverage too).
- Whether DDL parsing support should cover all index variants now or only the minimum needed parity for current planning goals.

## Likely codebase touchpoints
- codegen/schema.go
- codegen/loader.go
- codegen/generator.go
- codegen/generator_test.go
- codegen/loader_test.go
- README.md


